Students will complete the following questions to practice the skills they have learned in this lesson.
  1. Which of the following is equivalent to \(10^2−12^2\)?
  • \((10 + 12)(10 + 12)\)
  • \((10 − 12)(10 − 12)\)
  • \((10 −12)^2\)
  • \((10 + 12)(10 − 12)\)

Answer: \((10 + 12)(10 − 12)\)

For questions 2–10, select the expression in factored form.

  1. \(c^2 − 25\)
  • \(c(c − 25)\)
  • \((c − 5)(c − 5)\)
  • \((c − 5)(c + 5)\)
  • \((c + 5)(c + 5)\)

Answer: \((c − 5)(c + 5)\)

  1. \(9w^2 − 121\)
  • \((3w − 11)(3w + 11)\)
  • \((3w + 11)(3w + 11)\)
  • \(w(9w − 121)\)
  • \((3w − 11)(3w − 11)\)

Answer: \((3w − 11)(3w + 11)\)

  1. \(h^2− 121\)
  • \((h − 11)^2\)
  • \((h − 11)(h + 11)\)
  • \((h − 11)(h − 11)\)
  • \((h + 11)(h + 11)\)

Answer: \((h − 11)(h + 11)\)

  1. \(64 − d^2\)
  • \((8 − d)(8 − d)\)
  • \((8 − d)(8 + d)\)
  • \((8 + d)(8 + d)\)
  • Not possible

Answer: \((8 − d)(8 + d)\)

  1. \(4b^2 − 25\)
  • \((2b − 5)(2b + 5)\)
  • \((2b − 5)(2b − 5)\)
  • \(b(4b − 25)\)
  • \((2b + 5)(2b + 5)\)

Answer: \((2b − 5)(2b + 5)\)

  1. \(49 − 81z^2\)
  • \((7 + 9z)(7 + 9z)\)
  • \((7 − 9z)(7 − 9z)\)
  • \(z(49 − 81z)\)
  • \((7 − 9z)(7 + 9z)\)

Answer: \((7 − 9z)(7 + 9z)\)

  1. \(100y^2−4\)
  • \((10y + 2)(10y + 2)\)
  • \((10y − 2)(10y + 2)\)
  • \((10y − 2)(10y − 2)\)
  • Not possible

Answer: \((10y − 2)(10y + 2)\)

  1. \(x^2+9\)
  • \((x − 3)(x − 3)\)
  • \((x − 3)(x + 3)\)
  • \((x + 3)(x + 3)\)
  • Not possible

Answer: Not possible

  1. \(144 − 16g^2\)
  • \((12 − 4g)(12 + 4g)\)
  • \((12 + 4g)(12 + 4g)\)
  • \((12 − 4g)(12 − 4g)\)
  • Not possible

Answer: \((12 − 4g)(12 + 4g)\)
